rs for advice, boast that you had had your way and that at such a date and at such a place—Oh, you deserve to be shot!”—(growing din, clangor, and then again my voice)—“Much have you gained, idiot! The game’s up, you’ve blundered badly, not a groat will you see, baboon!” (crash of cymbals in the orchestra).

Thus I swore at him, with cold avidity observing the while his expression. He was utterly taken aback; and honestly offended. Pressing one hand to his breast, he kept shaking